</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC2FFD4FF1CF894BFCDC725" pageId="17" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC2FFD4FF1CF894BFCDC725" blockId="17.[136,1452,1733,2084]" pageId="17" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC2FFD4FF1CF894BE64C895" bold="true" box="[189,337,1913,1939]" pageId="17" pageNumber="238">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC2FFD4FECCF897BD37C892" box="[365,514,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="238">Spermogonia</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC2FFD4FDB8F897BD63C895" box="[537,598,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="238">aecia</emphasis>
and uredinia not found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC2FFD4FC33F894BCFCC895" box="[914,969,1913,1939]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="238">Telia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, compact, black, rounded to broadly elliptic, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC2FFD4FE40F870BD55C8B1" box="[481,608,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="238">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, mostly conical and rounded at apices, weakly constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 34.0–51.0 × 17.0–21.0 µm (av. 43.0 × 19.5 µm); walls brown, 0.6–1.4 µm (av. 0.9 µm) thick at sides, 5.4–8.6 µm (av. 6.9 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 19.5–48.0 µm (av. 32.0 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
